  "body": "# ðŸš€ Feature Request\r\n\r\n### Description\r\n\r\nIt has been brought up by @ferranbt that to avoid situations like #7827 , we could have a more graceful way to request blocks/logs in the event we do exceed the limit of eth1 provider.\r\n\r\n### Describe the solution you'd like\r\n\r\nThe solution would be similar to the one implemented here:\r\nhttps://github.com/umbracle/go-web3/blob/master/tracker/tracker.go#L344\r\n\r\nwhich uses a flow control(similar to TCP flow control) approach to auto adjust batch sizes for blocks/deposit logs. This allows for an easier user experience and also prevent the node from running into situations where it cannot start up at all due to restrictions implemented by the eth1 provider.\r\n\r\n",
